Global Funds Buy Net 5.8 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-05-26T03:29:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/global-funds-buy-net-5-8-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 5.8
billion rupees ($128 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1 percent to 1.041 trillion rupees, or 33.6
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 3.71 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
